rComments: The semester hasn't even ended but I had to come give Prof Teymouri the rating he deserves. He's probably my favourite prof ever, so nice and takes time to explain the details of what he's teaching. He makes the quizzes, assignments and midterm easier by telling you what to study. Would love to take another one of his classes. He's amazing!

He's really an amazing professor and wants to help you pass. The material was difficult as it was Stats but he made it easier to understand and overall was a great class and fun to attend. Would definitely recommend him as a professor.

Statistics, many students FAIL and work very hard to pass this course. It is not an easy course in general. Don't expect to find a prof who will give you free marks and boost your grade. You really have to work for it. Prof Teymouri is a sweet person but kind of slow at providing us resources to prep for tests in advance. Come prepared and goodluck

Really clear lectures and slides (both are posted), but the midterm was very difficult. Assignments (8 total, 5% each) are easy grade boosters. Takes forever to answer e-mails, but if you ask him a question at a lecture he'll break it down really well. Super nice guy and knows what he's talking about, would definitely take again.

HE IS AMAZING!!!! My absolute favourite Telfer Prof!. I had him for stats 2 and I absolutely loved him, and now I have him for ops. My fav lectures yet. He is amazing at explaining all content, and cares about his students success.
He is the best for ADM classes.

Amazing gem of a guy. Hes sweet and caring and wants the best for his students. If you have the chance to take any stats class with him, TAKE IT, since you will learn all you need to. The midterm and final required study time to excel in them which is the usual. The class is mainly content heavy but but easy to understand with Ahmad.

Very kind and knowledgeable professor. Extremely helpful if you have any questions, he will be more than willing to make sure you understand it fully. All professors should hold themselves to this standard. Online teaching is difficult but this prof uses that to his advantage to teach with virtual whiteboards.

Amazing professor and really understanding. Gives easy quizzes and gives extensions for assignments. gives lectures that are simple to understand. If you have any problems reach out to him and he'll respond quickly and help you out. Made a hard course seem easy. Absolute Gem of a professor.

Prof. Teymouri is genuinely one of the greatest teachers I've ever had. ATTEND ALL LECTURE (dgds optional). His lectures are very informative, I don't really like stats, but Prof. Teymouri changed that for me. I went to lectures, understood (easily) the content he taught, and now I've grown a liking to statistics.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Amazing lectures ']

rComments: Literally the business version of ElectroBOOM. Engaging lectures. Fair amount of homework, his slides do wonders but you still have to read the textbook if you want A+ for tests and the exam. Fair marking on the Case Study, plenty of time to work on it as well. Bonus questions for attendance were amazing.
One of the best profs I've had so far. He's a really good teacher and gives clear expectations on whats on the midterms and exams. If you have to take Stats, definitely pick him.

The easiest class I have ever taken. I didn't need to give so much effort to get A+. Attendance is not mandatory but if you want to get extra marks (4.5 marks), attend the lectures and do the quizzes. He is the best professor I have ever seen.
BEST PROFESSOR EVER !!!!!!!!!!!!!!
Great professor! Very easy final and quizzes. Gives upto 5% extra if you show up to all classes and do the in-class activities.

Prof. Teymouri is now one of my favorite university profs! He is lenient and he understands the struggle of online class. The quizzes and final were open book multiple choice and T/F questions. Take his class if you wanna boost up your GPA! He's very patient but don't push him especially if your questions can be answered by reading the syllabus!

GREATEST PROFESSOR YOU ARE EVER GOING TO GET. EVER. He fights for the students, he teaches SUPER well, his evaluations are fair. He wants us to succeed and HE SHOWS IT!! YOU JUST HAVE TO BE WITH HIM TO KNOW!!! Learning from him was a PLEASURE and an HONOUR! He's VERY patient but PLEASE DON'T exploit that!! Congrats on the Ph.D., Dr. Teymouri!!

Hands down best professor. Always cracks jokes and Truly genuinely cares about all the student success !! Outlines what is required to do well in the course and lives by it. Quizzes are very fair. Exam and quizzes are exactly the same as what he teaches in his lectures. If you couldn't get A on his class, you won't get forever with other Professor.
Amazing teacher! Makes you work for your grades but at the same time understands the struggles of online classes and even helped us with a few in class assignments.
Dudes, be so happy you got him as your teacher, and if you didnt, try to get him. That's it, nothing else to say.

Legit the nicest professor you would encounter. He is really caring, patient, and flexible with his students. He would answer all of the questions asked by his students to make sure you are on the right track!The class can honestly be boring and I also did not learn much though. I believe if the prof taught any other class it would be way better.

A very sweet, caring and patient prof. His lectures aren't too helpful though (just reading off the slides) and his quiz questions are worded in such a confusing way with more than one possible correct answer. Would not recommend if you're taking his class as an elective.
Great prof

Amazing lectures. Wonderful stories about his work experience. Very chill, extremely high patience. Assignments/quizzes are straightforward. Read the book/slides and success is guaranteed. If you have class with him, don't be rude/interrupt him, read the damn syllabus before asking a question. Please DO NOT take advantage of his patience.
One of the amazing professors I have ever seen. His lectures will help you a lot to answer his tests easily. He is a very caring and patient teacher so please DO NOT take advantage of his patience.

The nicest prof I've ever had. Prof Teymouri is so kind and patient and truly cares about his students succeeding. His quizzes are straightforward if you read the notes, he's not trying to trick anyone. No respondus, open book. Attend lecture for the in-class activities (easy bonus marks!). Nothing but love for this prof. Take his class if you can.

Taking his intro to business management right now, he is extremely kind and caring. He tries his best to make the class challenging, but responds to student feedback well and truly wants everyone to succeed. Probably the nicest prof at uottawa.

This guy does not know what he is talking about. His answers to his own quizzes are wrong. His multiple choice test questions have multiple correct answers and he doesn't even know which one is correct. Do not take his class if you have the choice
He is great!!!!
Great

Good prof with an easy course structure to follow. He did not give us a lot of info for the final, but the course was still relatively easy. Would recommend. Only used the textbook for the discussion group, which was all group work so as long as one person has the book you are golden.
